cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with neural handwriting recognition using deep learning models, specifically multi-dimensional long short-term memory (MDLSTM) recurrent neural networks. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The paper also focuses on developing efficient methods for MDLSTM-based models, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories.
